                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Turkey and the United States signed at Ankara on December 27, 1949, an agreement
                    (despatch 14, January 5, 1950, from Ankara, 511.823/1–550; <gloss
                        target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss> No. 2111, printed in 1 <gloss
                        target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 603; also, 98 <gloss target="#t_UNTS1"
                        >UNTS</gloss>
                    <pb facs="1263" n="1241" xml:id="pg_1241"/> 141) which, following its entry into
                    force on March 21, 1950, provided for the establishment of a United States
                    Educational Commission in Turkey to help administer an educational exchange
                    program authorized by Public Law 584, 79th Congress, the Fulbright Act, approved
                    August 1, 1946 (60 Stat. (pt. 11) 754).</p>
            </div>
